# Financial Risk Market Exposure Property Commercial Other Impairment ARF 320 0 Amount

## identifier
de8702

## status
Standard

## type
undefined

## definition
This is a balancing item in the list in which it is being used.
     
This is the value, as at the relevant date, of the amount of provisions for impairment of the reporting party's exposure to other commercial property, as required to be reported on APRA form ARF_230_0.
     
Commercial property exposure is defined according to the nature of the risk. An exposure should be classified as commercial property risk, if the exposure is subject to the performance of the property market.

